Yale Is Named No. 1 Seed in NCAA Hockey Tournament; North Dakota Is Second

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-03-21T04:00:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-21/yale-university-is-named-no-1-overall-seed-in-ncaa-hockey-tournament.html
Yale University  was named the
overall top seed in college hockey’s national tournament.  Yale will open its bid to win the National Collegiate
Athletic Association title for the first time against No. 16 Air
Force Academy on March 25 in Bridgeport,  Connecticut .  The Yale Bulldogs (27-6-1) beat Cornell 6-0 March 19 to win
the  ECAC Hockey  tournament championship. The Bulldogs, the
nation’s top-scoring team, have won four straight games and are
making their third consecutive visit to the NCAA tournament.  No. 2 North Dakota will begin tournament play against
Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute on March 26, third-ranked 
Boston College, the defending champion, plays Colorado College 
March 25 and No. 4 Miami of Ohio faces  New Hampshire , also on 
March 26.  The single-elimination tournament finishes with the
national championship on April 9 in Saint Paul, Minnesota.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dex McLuskey in Dallas  at
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net . 